/* Exercise Hints */
"Keep the phone at arm's length. Focus on the dot for 3 seconds, then shift your gaze to a distant object (across the room). Head stays still throughout." = "Keep the phone at arm's length. Focus on the dot for 3 seconds, then shift your gaze to a distant object (across the room). Head stays still throughout.";
"Follow the moving dot along the figure-eight path with your eyes only. Keep smooth, continuous movement — don't jump ahead." = "Follow the moving dot along the figure-eight path with your eyes only. Keep smooth, continuous movement — don't jump ahead.";
"Rub your palms together until warm, then gently cup them over your closed eyes. No pressure on the eyeballs. Breathe slowly and let your eyes relax in total darkness." = "Rub your palms together until warm, then gently cup them over your closed eyes. No pressure on the eyeballs. Breathe slowly and let your eyes relax in total darkness.";
"A dot lights up in one of 9 positions — jump your gaze to it immediately and hold for 2.5 seconds. Keep your head still; only move your eyes." = "A dot lights up in one of 9 positions — jump your gaze to it immediately and hold for 2.5 seconds. Keep your head still; only move your eyes.";
"Look straight ahead, face relaxed. Slowly close eyelids fully — no squinting. Hold 1 second. Open slowly. Repeat every 5 seconds." = "Look straight ahead, face relaxed. Slowly close eyelids fully — no squinting. Hold 1 second. Open slowly. Repeat every 5 seconds.";
"Place a small sticker on a window at eye level. Stand arm's length away. Focus on the dot for 10 seconds, then shift to a distant object outside for 10 seconds." = "Place a small sticker on a window at eye level. Stand arm's length away. Focus on the dot for 10 seconds, then shift to a distant object outside for 10 seconds.";
"Hold phone at arm's length, focus on the center dot. Slowly bring it toward your nose, keeping the dot single and clear. When it doubles, move back out." = "Hold phone at arm's length, focus on the center dot. Slowly bring it toward your nose, keeping the dot single and clear. When it doubles, move back out.";
"Follow the dot as it traces a square with your eyes. Direction alternates clockwise then counterclockwise each lap." = "Follow the dot as it traces a square with your eyes. Direction alternates clockwise then counterclockwise each lap.";
"Follow the dot: slowly up — pause — down — pause. 10 repetitions. Then left — pause — right — pause. 10 repetitions." = "Follow the dot: slowly up — pause — down — pause. 10 repetitions. Then left — pause — right — pause. 10 repetitions.";
"Apply a warm, damp cloth over closed eyes. The heat helps open oil glands in your eyelids. Breathe deeply and relax for 3 minutes." = "Apply a warm, damp cloth over closed eyes. The heat helps open oil glands in your eyelids. Breathe deeply and relax for 3 minutes.";
"Two circles will appear side by side. Relax your eyes and let them slowly merge into one. When you see a single circle, hold your focus." = "Two circles will appear side by side. Relax your eyes and let them slowly merge into one. When you see a single circle, hold your focus.";
"Similar to stereogram, but the circles move apart and back together. Try to maintain fusion (single image) as long as possible." = "Similar to stereogram, but the circles move apart and back together. Try to maintain fusion (single image) as long as possible.";
"Sit upright, relax shoulders. Inhale 6 seconds — slowly raise your gaze. Hold 2 seconds at top. Exhale 7 seconds — lower your gaze. Repeat." = "Sit upright, relax shoulders. Inhale 6 seconds — slowly raise your gaze. Hold 2 seconds at top. Exhale 7 seconds — lower your gaze. Repeat.";
"Every 20 minutes, look at something 20 feet away for 20 seconds. This exercise is a single guided 20-second break." = "Every 20 minutes, look at something 20 feet away for 20 seconds. This exercise is a single guided 20-second break.";
"Using a fingertip, gently massage your upper eyelid from the temple toward the nose. Then do the same on the lower lid. Light pressure only." = "Using a fingertip, gently massage your upper eyelid from the temple toward the nose. Then do the same on the lower lid. Light pressure only.";
"Squeeze your eyes shut firmly for 2 seconds, then open wide for 2 seconds. This strengthens orbicularis and levator muscles." = "Squeeze your eyes shut firmly for 2 seconds, then open wide for 2 seconds. This strengthens orbicularis and levator muscles.";
"Perform a slow, complete blink — close fully, hold 1 second, open. Then look at a distant point for 4 seconds. Repeat." = "Perform a slow, complete blink — close fully, hold 1 second, open. Then look at a distant point for 4 seconds. Repeat.";

/* Exercise Indications */
"Great for people who work at a screen 6+ hours/day. Helps with nearsightedness prevention, eye focusing fatigue, and Computer Vision Syndrome." = "Great for people who work at a screen 6+ hours/day. Helps with nearsightedness prevention, eye focusing fatigue, and Computer Vision Syndrome.";
"Improves eye mobility and coordination. Helpful for people with restricted eye movement, or those recovering after eye muscle procedures." = "Improves eye mobility and coordination. Helpful for people with restricted eye movement, or those recovering after eye muscle procedures.";
"Instant relief for tired, overworked eyes. Recommended after long screen sessions or any time your eyes feel strained." = "Instant relief for tired, overworked eyes. Recommended after long screen sessions or any time your eyes feel strained.";
"Helps with reading speed and accuracy. Useful for anyone who loses their place while reading or has trouble with quick eye movements." = "Helps with reading speed and accuracy. Useful for anyone who loses their place while reading or has trouble with quick eye movements.";
"Restores your natural blink rate, which drops 60% during screen use. Helps with dry, irritated eyes and eye fatigue." = "Restores your natural blink rate, which drops 60% during screen use. Helps with dry, irritated eyes and eye fatigue.";
"Classic optometry exercise for focusing flexibility. Great for people with accommodative insufficiency or early presbyopia symptoms." = "Classic optometry exercise for focusing flexibility. Great for people with accommodative insufficiency or early presbyopia symptoms.";
"Strengthens eye teaming. Helps with convergence insufficiency — common in people who get headaches or double vision while reading." = "Strengthens eye teaming. Helps with convergence insufficiency — common in people who get headaches or double vision while reading.";
"Strengthens all six eye muscles evenly. Especially helpful for people with eye movement asymmetry or post-surgical recovery." = "Strengthens all six eye muscles evenly. Especially helpful for people with eye movement asymmetry or post-surgical recovery.";
"Builds range of motion in all four cardinal directions. Good for people with restricted gaze or neck tension from screen use." = "Builds range of motion in all four cardinal directions. Good for people with restricted gaze or neck tension from screen use.";
"Recommended by ophthalmologists for dry eye and meibomian gland dysfunction. The heat liquefies blocked oils to restore your tear film." = "Recommended by ophthalmologists for dry eye and meibomian gland dysfunction. The heat liquefies blocked oils to restore your tear film.";
"Trains your brain to fuse images from both eyes. Helps develop stereoscopic depth perception and binocular vision." = "Trains your brain to fuse images from both eyes. Helps develop stereoscopic depth perception and binocular vision.";
"Advanced binocular training. Builds flexible vergence — the ability to maintain single vision at changing distances." = "Advanced binocular training. Builds flexible vergence — the ability to maintain single vision at changing distances.";
"Combines eye movement with breathing rhythm. Reduces overall tension, lowers intraocular pressure, and calms the nervous system." = "Combines eye movement with breathing rhythm. Reduces overall tension, lowers intraocular pressure, and calms the nervous system.";
"The AAO's #1 recommendation for screen users. Prevents accommodative spasm and reduces digital eye strain." = "The AAO's #1 recommendation for screen users. Prevents accommodative spasm and reduces digital eye strain.";
"Stimulates meibomian glands to produce healthy oils. Based on TFOS DEWS II dry eye management guidelines." = "Stimulates meibomian glands to produce healthy oils. Based on TFOS DEWS II dry eye management guidelines.";
"Builds eyelid muscle tone for better blink quality. Recommended for incomplete blinkers and people with lagophthalmos risk." = "Builds eyelid muscle tone for better blink quality. Recommended for incomplete blinkers and people with lagophthalmos risk.";
"Restores tear film stability. Combines intentional blinking with distance relaxation, per TFOS DEWS II guidelines." = "Restores tear film stability. Combines intentional blinking with distance relaxation, per TFOS DEWS II guidelines.";

